    Suppose that, on any finite Ã©tale covering of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> does not admit a constant abelian subscheme.
    Then, for every abelian scheme <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  Y\to  S]]></fr:tex>, we have
    <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       \begin {aligned}         \operatorname {Hom}(X,Y)         &\xrightarrow {\sim } \operatorname {Hom}(\mathrm {R}_1f_*\mathbb {Z},\mathrm {R}_1g_*\mathbb {Z})       \\\operatorname {Hom}(Y,X)         &\xrightarrow {\sim } \operatorname {Hom}(\mathrm {R}_1g_*\mathbb {Z},\mathrm {R}_1f_*\mathbb {Z}).       \end {aligned}     ]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
  
    
