        <fr:p>If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Z]]></fr:tex> is completely imaginary, and not imaginary quadratic, then we must have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a=2g=4]]></fr:tex>.
          For <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s\in  S]]></fr:tex>, the centraliser of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Z]]></fr:tex> acting on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathrm {R}_1f_*\mathbb {Q})_s]]></fr:tex> is thus commutative, and so the action of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\pi _1(S,s)]]></fr:tex> is abelian, and thus factors through a finite group ((iii.b) of <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.8"
