    <fr:p>We will show that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> satisfies the conditions of <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-4.4.12"
href="hodge-theory-ii-4.4.12.xml"
taxon="Proposition"
number="4.4.12" />.
      If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Z]]></fr:tex> is imaginary quadratic, and if there exists <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\rho \colon  Z\to \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {R}_1f_*\mathbb {Q}\otimes _{Z,\rho }\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> is of pure Hodge type <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(-1,0)]]></fr:tex>, then the Hodge structure on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {R}_1f_*\mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex> is locally constant, which is a contradiction.
      This proves <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-4.4.13"
